n a fiscally responsible manner, there is no reason they can’t both be in effect simultaneously. ";}i:2;i:3907;}i:50;a:3:{i:0;s:7:"p_close";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:4354;}i:51;a:3:{i:0;s:13:"section_close";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:4356;}i:52;a:3:{i:0;s:6:"header";i:1;a:3:{i:0;s:7:"Summary";i:1;i:2;i:2;i:4356;}i:2;i:4356;}i:53;a:3:{i:0;s:12:"section_open";i:1;a:1:{i:0;i:2;}i:2;i:4356;}i:54;a:3:{i:0;s:6:"p_open";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:4356;}i:55;a:3:{i:0;s:5:"cdata";i:1;a:1:{i:0;s:465:"After years of consideration the Board feels strongly that putting the mechanism in place to pay Patronage Dividends is in the best interest of the Co-op. In addition to being a mechanism to distribute profits to members, it is also serves to minimize income tax liabilities in a legal and ethical way.
